        "cmip6.aerosol.key_properties.overview": {
            "values": [
                "The 4-mode version of Modal Aerosol Model (MAM4) in CESM2 includes 4 aerosol modes: Aitken, accumulation, coarse and primary carbon modes and is fully described in Liu_2016. The number concentrations of each mode as well as the mass mixing ratios of aerosol components in each mode are predicted. Aerosol components within each mode are internally mixed while those between modes are externally mixed. Processes affecting aerosol properties (e.g., size, mass, number) are treated in MAM4, including emission, nucleation, condensation, coagulation, wet and dry deposition, and gas and aqueous-phase production."
            ]
        }, 
        "cmip6.aerosol.key_properties.scheme_scope": {
            "values": [
                "Whole atmosphere"
            ]
        }, 
        "cmip6.aerosol.key_properties.basic_approximations": {
            "values": [
                "Modal. Describes 4 modes with a mass and number. Internal mixtures. "
            ]
        }, 
