        "cmip6.aerosol.optical_radiative_properties.cloud_interactions.overview": {
            "values": [
                "Aerosol activation is physcially represented and based on the aerosol size distribution, hygroscopicity, and updraft velocity. Thus aerosol changes in number concentrations are allowed to affect cloud droplet number concentrations. Activated aerosols will be transferred to the cloud-borne aerosol, also treated in the model. With the formation of precipitation, cloud-borne aerosols will be removed. Thus the two-way aerosol-cloud interactions are considered. Aerosols are also allowed to affect ice and mixed-phase clouds by ice nucleation. These aerosols will also be removed when the ice crystals precipitate."
            ]
        }, 
